rules: Rule1: Either person1 has food1 ready for harvest or person2 has food1 ready for harvest.
Rule2: Under the condition that food1 has been packaged, it is sealed.
Rule3: Food1 is packaged or food1 is labeled.
Rule4: In the event that food1 is labeled, then either food1 is stored in region3 or, if the absence of inspection leading to contamination does not trigger a recall, food1 is distributed.
Rule5: Given that food1 is sealed, either it is stored in region3 or, provided that the absence of inspection leading to contamination does not lead to a recall, it is distributed.
Rule6: If food1 is temperature-controlled, then should food1 not be safe, it is not expired.
Rule7: Either food1 is temperature-controlled or food1 is refrigerated.
Rule8: Under the condition that food1 is frozen, if food1 is not safe, it is not expired.
Rule9: Should person2 have food1 ready for harvest, food1 is safe.
Rule10: Either a preservative is added to food1 or food1 is vacuum-sealed.
Rule11: Given that food1 is vacuum-sealed, if preservation is applied, then if it is refrigerated, it is frozen.
Rule12: If food1 is safety-certified, then it is approved for sale.
Rule13: Either food1 is organic-certified or, if food1 is safety-certified, then provided a preservative is added, should preservation be applied, if it is refrigerated, it is frozen.
Rule14: Whenever microbial activity is detected in food1, then if bacterial growth is present, under the condition that mold growth occurs, food1 is spoiled.
Rule15: Either a temperature breach has occurred for food1 or a humidity breach has occurred for food1.
Rule16: Given that a humidity breach has occurred for food1, microbial activity is detected in food1.
Rule17: Under the condition that material1 is prepared to transport food1, food1 is safe.
Rule18: Either pest infestation affects food1 or, if a temperature breach occurs, microbial activity is detected.
Rule19: Rodent damage is present on food1 or pest infestation does not affect food1.
Rule20: Either person3 has verified the supplier of food1 or person4 has verified the producer of food1.
Rule21: Should person4 verify the producer of food1, then if processing is complete in region1, provided that person1 has food1 ready for harvest, transport readiness with material1 follows.

Rule22: If the origin of food1 is traced to region4, then under the condition that person3 verifies the supplier, whenever processing is complete in region1, if person1 has food1 ready for harvest, material1 is prepared to transport it.
Rule23: Whenever food1 is exported, it is imported.
Rule24: If food1 is domestic, then it is exported.
Rule25: Provided that food1 has cleared customs, then if its origin is not traced to region4, it is domestic.
Rule26: If food1 requires quarantine, then should its origin not be traced to region4, it is domestic.
Rule27: If processing is complete in region1 for food1, then it is quality-approved.
Rule28: Either processing is complete in region1 for food1 or processing is complete in region2 for food1.
Rule29: Provided that food1 meets regulatory standards, if it has not cleared customs or does not require quarantine, then it is restricted.
Rule30: Either food1 meets regulatory standards or food1 violates standards.
Rule31: If food1 violates standards, then under the condition that it has not cleared customs or does not require quarantine, it is restricted.

Rule32: Provided that the calorie content of food1 is verified, if processing is complete in region1, then under the condition that person1 has food1 ready for harvest, material1 is prepared to transport it.
Rule33: If food1 has been safety-audited, then compliance has been verified for food1.
Rule34: If compliance has been verified for food1, then certification for food1 has been renewed.
Rule35: Under the condition that certification for food1 has been renewed, if an allergen is undeclared, then food1 is not mislabeled.
Rule36: Should processing be complete in region2 for food1, then if person1 has food1 ready for harvest, material1 is prepared to transport it.
Rule37: Whenever food1 has been withdrawn from the market, then either it has been recalled by the producer or it is not banned.
Rule38: If a retailer has rejected food1, then either it has been recalled by the producer or it is not banned.
Rule39: Provided that a consumer complaint has been filed about food1, it has been withdrawn from the market.
Rule40: If a quality issue is present with food1, then a retailer has rejected food1.
Rule41: Either a lawsuit has been filed regarding food1 or, if neither a consumer complaint nor a quality issue occurs, an investigation is launched.
Rule42: Under the condition that food1 is quality-approved, if person1 has food1 ready for harvest, transport readiness with material1 follows.
Rule43: If compensation has been paid for food1, then a refund has been issued for food1.
Rule44: Provided that a shortage of food1 has occurred, the price of food1 has increased.
Rule45: If a shortage of food1 has occurred, then a substitute has been used for food1.
Rule46: Either a shortage of food1 has occurred or the supply of food1 is not disrupted.
Rule47: If a substitute has been used for food1, then the price of food1 has not increased.
Rule48: If food1 has been donated, then it has been redistributed.
Rule49: Provided that food1 has been redistributed, it has been repurposed.
Rule50: If it is not the case that if food1 is refrigerated then it is frozen, then the supply of food1 is disrupted.
Rule51: If it is not the case that if food1 has undergone nutrition testing then its calorie content is verified, then food1 is mislabeled.
Rule52: Provided that it is not true that if nutrition testing occurs then calorie verification follows, an allergen is undeclared on food1.
Rule53: If it is not the case that if food1 is approved for sale then, provided a preservative is added, whenever preservation is applied, refrigeration leads to freezing, then food1 is banned.
Rule54: Provided that it is not the case that either a consumer complaint or a quality issue happens, an investigation is not launched.
Rule55: If it is not true that if food1 is composted then waste is not generated, then food1 has been disposed of in a landfill.
Rule56: Under the condition that the implication from composting to no waste generation fails, food1 has been recycled.
Rule57: If the implication from recycling to no landfill disposal does not hold, food1 has been donated.
Rule58: Under the condition that recycling does not imply absence of landfill disposal, food1 has not been repurposed.
Rule59: If it is not true that inspection leads to no contamination, then food1 is not recalled.
Rule60: If the implication from not safe to not expired fails, compensation has been paid for food1.
Rule61: Under the condition that the absence of safety does not imply no expiration, waste has been generated from food1.
Rule62: Should it not be true that if food1 is not safe then it is not expired, a refund has not been issued.
Rule63: If food1 is not safe, then it has expired.
Rule64: Whenever food1 is not safe, mold growth is present on food1.
Rule65: If food1 is not safe, then it is contaminated.
Rule66: Under the condition that food1 is not safe, it has been inspected.
